name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $identifier
desc: Returns: A formal identifier that is used to identify this code system when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance.

desc: A formal identifier that is used to identify this code system when it is represented in other formats, or referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance.

name: $::name
desc: Returns: A natural language name identifying the subscription.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A natural language name identifying the subscription.

name: $status
desc: Returns: The status of the subscription, which marks the server state for managing the subscription.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The status of the subscription, which marks the server state for managing the subscription.

name: $topic
desc: Returns: The reference to the topic to be notified about.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The reference to the topic to be notified about.

name: $contact
desc: Returns: Contact details for a human to contact about the subscription. The primary use of this for system administrator troubleshooting.

desc: Contact details for a human to contact about the subscription. The primary use of this for system administrator troubleshooting.

lvardefs.name: objRef

name: $end
desc: Returns: The time for the server to turn the subscription off.

name: $reason
desc: Returns: A description of why this subscription is defined.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A description of why this subscription is defined.

name: $filterBy
desc: Returns: The filter properties to be applied to narrow the topic stream.  When multiple filters are applied, evaluates to true if all the conditions are met; otherwise it returns false.   (i.e., logical AND).

name: $addfilterBy
desc: The filter properties to be applied to narrow the topic stream.  When multiple filters are applied, evaluates to true if all the conditions are met; otherwise it returns false.   (i.e., logical AND).

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: The filter properties to be applied to narrow the topic stream.  When multiple filters are applied, evaluates to true if all the conditions are met; otherwise it returns false.   (i.e., logical AND).

name: $error
desc: Returns: A record of the last error that occurred when the server processed a notification.

name: $adderror
desc: A record of the last error that occurred when the server processed a notification.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: A record of the last error that occurred when the server processed a notification.

name: $eventCount
desc: Returns: A record of  the number of events for which the server has attempted delivery on this subscription (i.e., the number of events that occurred while the subscription is in an "active" or "error" state -- not "requested" or "off").   Server Initializes to 0 for a new subscription.  Repeated attempts at delivery of the *same* event notification do not increment this counter.  Valid values are unsigned integers (0+).  The decmial type is used to ensure that counts can grow larger than 32-bit values.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A record of  the number of events for which the server has attempted delivery on this subscription (i.e., the number of events that occurred while the subscription is in an "active" or "error" state -- not "requested" or "off").   Server Initializes to 0

name: $channel
desc: Returns: Details where to send notifications when resources are received that meet the criteria.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Details where to send notifications when resources are received that meet the criteria.
